I"<p>For young students, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memetic-psychotherapy-equips-prefrontal-areas-with-mental-tools-for-managing-limbic-friction">framing</a> math problems as a social situation improves performance. The underlying cause might be a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/rich-mental-model-repository-is-conductive-of-insight">transfer of useful conceptual structures</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/how-can-you-acquire-tacit-knowledge-effectively">from the social realm</a>.</p>
